n/Business Insider\r\n<ul><li>I\'ve spent 120 hours on six overnight train rides in the US and Europe. </li><li… [+2977 chars]','2023-11-27 16:32:08',1,'2023-12-25 17:08:18','2023-12-25 17:08:18'),(93,'Why the World Needs Its Own Immune System','why-the-world-needs-its-own-immune-system',81,4,14,'We should seize the moment right now to build a new set of protections against future public health crises.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/12/25/opinion/global-immune-system-public-health.html','https://via.placeholder.com/150','\n        <div class=\'article-content\'>\n            <h5 class=\'article-content__text\'>\n                The thing that has surprised me most since I began my job leading foreign assistance for global health at the U.S. Agency for International Development is how much emergencies have defined my work. The bureau I oversee focuses on reducing the global burden of mortality and disease and on protecting the United States from health threats from abroad. Our work is supposed to primarily serve long-range goals — for instance, eradicating polio (after 35 years of effort, we’re down to just a handful of wild-type cases in the world) and ending the public health threat of H.I.V., malaria and tuberculosis by 2030. But from the moment I started, more immediate problems have diverted time, attention and resources.\n            </h5>\n            <div>\n            <p class=\'snipit-class\'>\n                We should seize the moment right now to build a new set of protections against future public health crises.\n            </p>\n            </div>\n        </div>','2023-12-25 09:00:10',1,'2023-12-25 17:08:22','2023-12-25 17:08:22'),(94,'Elon Musk\'s newest phase is cosplaying as a savior-statesman','elon-musks-newest-phase-is-cosplaying-as-a-savior-statesman',82,1,5,'While American CEOs have expressed strong support for Israel, none have so publicly straddled the line between diplomacy and business in this way.','https://www.businessinsider.com/elon-musk-is-cosplaying-as-statesman-in-israel-visit-2023-11','https://i.insider.com/6565d3f9c58b6f84123ad778?width=1200&format=jpeg','Billionaire and boss of the social network X, Elon Musk, in Israel with prime minister Benjamin Netanyahi (center) and officials on November 27.Amos Ben-Gershom (GPO) Handout via Getty Images\r\n<ul><l… [+5210 chars]','2023-11-28 09:01:10',1,'2023-12-25 17:08:23','2023-12-25 17:08:23'),(95,'N.I.H.’s New Leader Wants to Broaden Participation in Medical Research','nihs-new-leader-wants-to-broaden-participation-in-medical-research',83,4,14,'In a wide-ranging interview, Dr. Monica M. Bertagnolli, the director of the National Institutes of Health, discussed drug patents, trust in science and her own experience as a cancer patient.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/12/25/us/politics/monica-bertagnolli-nih.html','https://via.placeholder.com/150','\n        <div class=\'article-content\'>\n            <h5 class=\'article-content__text\'>\n                When Dr. Monica M. Bertagnolli moved into the director’s suite at the National Institutes of Health, she brought with her a single piece of art, a lithograph created by the granddaughter of a cancer patient she once treated. It depicts an abstract geometric female figure and the organs she lost to cancer. Its title: “We Are Not What You Have Taken: A Response to Cancer.”\n            </h5>\n            <div>\n            <p class=\'snipit-class\'>\n                In a wide-ranging interview, Dr. Monica M. Bertagnolli, the director of the National Institutes of Health, discussed drug patents, trust in science and her own experience as a cancer patient.\n            </p>\n            </div>\n        </div>','2023-12-25 05:00:53',1,'2023-12-25 17:08:27','2023-12-25 17:08:27'),(96,'Here\'s some of the best advice offered by late investing legend Charlie Munger','heres-some-of-the-best-advice-offered-by-late-investing-legend-charlie-munger',84,1,5,'This is some of the best advice offered by the late inve