e two countries to take part over the objections of Ukraine and others.\n            </p>\n            </div>\n        </div>','2023-12-08 11:39:02',1,'2023-12-25 17:10:30','2023-12-25 17:10:30'),(142,'Amazon’s \'Q\' Is Less AI Conspiracy, More Corporate Chatbot','amazons-q-is-less-ai-conspiracy-more-corporate-chatbot',124,1,18,'Amazon is throwing its e-commerce bulk into the AI game like an enormous capybara stampeding into the outside lane of the ongoing AI rat race. The company finally shared details of its new AI chatbot assistant dubbed “Q” at its AWS re:Invent event on Tuesday.…','https://gizmodo.com/amazon-announces-corporate-chatbot-q-1851055654','https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fill,h_675,pg_1,q_80,w_1200/a5f4080db42d06610cd17673cdc747ac.jpg','Amazon is throwing its e-commerce bulk into the AI game like an enormous capybara stampeding into the outside lane of the ongoing AI rat race. The company finally shared details of its new AI chatbot… [+2984 chars]','2023-11-28 16:10:00',1,'2023-12-25 17:10:35','2023-12-25 17:10:35'),(143,'The Missing Piece of the Premier League’s TV Rights Deal','the-missing-piece-of-the-premier-leagues-tv-rights-deal',125,6,14,'Why did soccer’s richest league step back from streaming? Maybe because the status quo still pays.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/12/08/world/europe/premier-leagues-tv-rights.html','https://via.placeholder.com/150','\n        <div class=\'article-content\'>\n            <h5 class=\'article-content__text\'>\n                The technical term might be “vertical integration.” Or, on reflection, perhaps that is not quite right, and it would — in the jargon — be known as “synergy.” Maybe those are the same thing. Either way, the concept is best encapsulated by Jack Donaghy, the vulpine executive portrayed by Alec Baldwin in the presumably now problematic sitcom “30 Rock.”\n            </h5>\n            <div>\n            <p class=\'snipit-class\'>\n                Why did soccer’s richest league step back from streaming? Maybe because the status quo still pays.\n            </p>\n            </div>\n        </div>','2023-12-08 11:45:27',1,'2023-12-25 17:10:36','2023-12-25 17:10:36'),(144,'Essential AI emerges from stealth with backing from Google, Nvidia and AMD','essential-ai-emerges-from-stealth-with-backing-from-google-nvidia-and-amd',126,1,19,'Essential AI says the products would make data analysts 10x faster and give business users the ability to become data-driven decision-makers.','https://venturebeat.com/ai/essential-ai-emerges-from-stealth-with-backing-from-google-nvidia-and-amd/','https://venturebeat.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/ashish_vaswani_and_niki_parmar__essential_ai___andrew_gessler_-_1.jpg?w=1200&strip=all','Are you ready to bring more awareness to your brand? Consider becoming a sponsor for The AI Impact Tour. Learn more about the opportunities here.\r\nSan Francisco-based Essential AI, a startup looking … [+1440 chars]','2023-12-12 10:55:39',1,'2023-12-25 17:10:40','2023-12-25 17:10:40'),(145,'For Sports Illustrated, Report About Fake Authors Is Latest Stumble','for-sports-illustrated-report-about-fake-authors-is-latest-stumble',127,6,14,'The venerable magazine has experienced management upheaval and staff complaints in recent years. Now there’s a question over who wrote product reviews on its site.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/11/28/business/sports-illustrated-artifical-intelligence.html','https://via.placeholder.com/150','\n        <div class=\'article-content\'>\n            <h5 class=\'article-content__text\'>\n                Three years ago, journalists at Sports Illustrated were worried that the venerable magazine’s new owners and operators were drastically lowering its standards. They noted reports of plagiarism, and worried about substandard writing and the use of freelance reporters with little due diligence. The journalists also wanted better pay, greater transparency during the hiring process and a guarantee that all work published on the Sports Illustrated website would be edited.\n            </h5>\n            <div>\n            <p class=\'snipit-class\'>\n                The venerable magazine has experienced management upheaval and staff complaints in recent years. Now there’s a question over who wrote product reviews on its site.\n            </p>\n            </div>\n        </div>','2023-11-28 16:07:28',1,'2023-12-25 17:10:41','2023-12-25 17:10:41'),(146,'Google’s App Store Monopoly Ruled Illegal as Jury Sides With Epic','googles-app-store-monopoly-ruled-illegal-as-jury-sides-with-epic',52,1,3,'A jury in San Francisco unanimously found that Google stifled competition for its app store. A judge will now decide on what fixes to require at the company, but appeals could delay the impact of the case for years.','https://www.wired.com/story/googles-app-store-monopoly-ruled-illegal-jury-epic/','https://media.wired.com/photos/657779c5115a4e9fcb097567/191:100/w_1280,c_limit/Google-v-Epic-Games-Lawsuit-Business-624873222.jpg','Google violated antitrust laws through deals that stifled competition for its Play mobile app store, a jury in San Francisco unanimously found today. The verdict delivers the first significant US cou… [+1561 chars]','2023-12-11 19:41:09',1,'2023-12-25 17:10:45','2023-12-25 17:10:45'),(147,'N.C.A.A. Proposes Uncapping Compensation for Athletes','ncaa-proposes-uncapping-compensation-for-athletes',113,6,14,'Under the plan, schools would set aside educational trust funds of at least $30,000 per year for at least half of their athletes, and would have to comply with Title IX laws.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/12/05/us/ncaa-athlete-compensation-cap-proposal.html','https://via.placeholder.com/150','\n        <div class=\'article-content\'>\n            <h5 class=\'article-content__text\'>\n                A plan by the N.C.A.A. for a series of reforms that includes uncapped compensation for athletes could help address the growing inequities of a system in which sports like football and men’s basketball generate billions in television and other revenue yet the schools share a minuscule amount directly with the athletes.\n            </h5>\n            <div>\n            <p class=\'snipit-class\'>\n                Under the plan, schools would set aside educational trust funds of at least $30,000 per year for at least half of their athletes, and would have to comply with Title IX laws.\n            </p>\n            </div>\n        </div>','2023-12-05 15:57:26',1,'2023-12-25 17:10:46','2023-12-25 17:10:46'),(148,'Some business leaders like Jeff Bezos hate the phrase \'work-life balance.\' Here\'s what they prefer instead.','some-business-leaders-like-jeff-bezos-hate-the-phrase-work-life-balance-heres-what-they-prefer-instead',128,1,5,'Jeff Bezos calls work-life balance a \"debilitating\" phrase. TIAA\'s CEO calls it a \"lie.\" Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella prefers \"work-life harmony.\"','https://www.businessinsider.com/ceos-who-hate-phrase-work-life-balance-prefer-alternative-views-2023-11','https://i.insider.com/656317b6fd6200867dcf4a6b?width=1200&format=jpeg','Work-life balance seems like it wouldn\'t be controversial, but some of the nation\'s top CEOs aren\'t big fans of the term.Photo by Lucas Schifres/Getty Images\r\n<ul>\n<li>Over the years, CEOs and busine… [+4851 chars]','2023-11-26 04:51:02',1,'2023-12-25 17:10:50','2023-12-25 17:10:50'),(149,'The 2023 Good Tech Awards','the-2023-good-tech-awards',129,7,14,'Toasting a year of breakthroughs (and a few breakdowns) in Silicon Valley and beyond.','https://www.nytimes.com/2023/12/25/technology/the-2023-good-tech-awards.html','https://via.placeholder.com/150','\n        <div class=\'article-content\'>\n            <h5 class=\'article-content__text\'>\n                In the tech industry, 2023 was a year of transformation.\n            </h5>\n            <div>\n            <p class=\'snipit-class\'>\n                Toasting a year of breakthroughs (and a few breakdowns) in Silicon Va